        If you have questions or concerns with the procedures or content pertaining to this website please contact our office at 877-NYBECKUSA (692-3258).</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.4em; font-weight:bold; color:#f7c815; margin:10px 0 0 0;">Information Collected and Used</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;">In order to take part in ProDriver services, obtain information from ProDriver or have questions answered by ProDriver, ProDriver may request and/or collect personal information that may include, without limitation, your first and last name, home address, phone number, email address, drivers licenses, current medical card or long form , social security number and other information needed to create a DOT certified driver qualification (DQ) file. By entering Personal Information on the Site, you consent to our use of the Personal Information for purposes related to the Site and the services offered and/or provided on or in connection with the Site. This applies to the Fair Credit Reporting Act Section 604(b)(2)(a), public law 91-508 as it was amended by the CCRA of 1996, (title 2)(subtitle D)(Chapter 1) of( public law 104-208) you are being informed that reports verifying your previous employment, drug and alcohol test results and your driving records may be obtained for employment purposes. These reports are required by section 382.413 and 391.25 of the FMCSA. Without limiting the foregoing, by giving us Personal Information you are giving us permission to contact you and/or send you promotional and/or other information about services and offerings from ProDriver.</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.4em; font-weight:bold; color:#f7c815; margin:10px 0 0 0;">Control</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;">You have the right to review, correct and offer rebuttal to all information gathered by ProDriver as it pertains to our research. You also understand that by giving false and misleading information may result in loss of use to the Prodriver site as well as termination of work gained through this site. You may choose to opt out of the participation of  ProDriver at any time. You may contact direct by phone by calling 877-NYBECKUSA (692-3258) or send an email to support@prodiver-online.com and request your file to be deleted from the program. You may also request all files that have been submitted to be returned or destroyed. ProDriver understands that from time to time you may wish to suspend your account and have your profile removed from the database search process but may want to reinstate your membership at a later date. We would require an email or written documentation requesting account suspention and retention of profile information via support@prodive-online.com.</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.4em; font-weight:bold; color:#f7c815; margin:10px 0 0 0;">Information Sharing</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;"><strong>ProDriver will never resell your personal identifying information for marketing or demographic solicitation. </strong>ProDriver collects information from its members in order to create a profile. ProDriver may share certain Personal Information collected within the Site in order to perform database searches with its prescreened companies. <strong>Information collected by ProDriver to be transferred upon request is the sole responsibility of the members.</strong> Personal Identifying information uploaded to the site is for storage and is only accessible by the member themselves. Members have to agree and perform the act of giving their DQ to the prescreened member company.</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.4em; font-weight:bold; color:#f7c815; margin:10px 0 0 0;">Security</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;">ProDriver uses industry-standard security measures to protect certain Personal Information. However, no data transmitted over or accessible through the public Internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. As a result, while we attempt to protect Personal Information, ProDriver cannot ensure or warrant that Personal Information will be completely secure from misappropriation by hackers or from other nefarious or criminal activities, or in the event of a failure of computer hardware, software, or a telecommunications network. At this time no personal information is stored on static servers, cloud servers or other shared ISP equipment. The transfer of information is stored as hard copy files until time of request by a verified user. Files are transmitted digitally to the user with permission of the driver at the time of request.</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.4em; font-weight:bold; color:#f7c815; margin:10px 0 0 0;">Driver Application Employment Disclaimer</div>
        <div style="font-size:1.2em; color:#fff; margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:20px;">By signing and/or submitting this application I certify that I personally completed this application and that all of the information is true and correct. I hereby request and authorize ProDriver-Online Inc and their agents or contractors that receive this application to cause to be conducted, at any time, an investigation of my background for employment purposes, which may include, but is not limited to, any information relating to my character, general reputation, personal characteristics, mode of living, criminal history, past work experience, educational background, alcohol or drug test results, or failure to submit to an alcohol or drug test, driving record, or any other information about me which may reflect upon my potential for employment gathered from any individual, organization, entity, agency, or other source which may have knowledge concerning any such items of information. I have completed this application of my own free will and hold harmless of all liability all companies, agents and associated parties for the use of this application</div>
